Section 1. That section 2923.24 of the Revised Code be 5
amended to read as follows: 6
Sec. 2923.24. (A) As used in this section, "electronic 7
device or tool" means a device or tool designed or adapted for 8
use in unlocking or turning on a motor vehicle and does not 9
include a previously issued or activated electronic card, key, 10
or other electronic device assigned to the lawful owner of a 11
motor vehicle. 12
(B) No person shall possess or have under the person's 13
control any substance, device, instrument, or article, with 14
purpose to use it criminally. 15
(B)(C) Each of the following constitutes prima-facie 16
evidence of criminal purpose: 17
(1) Possession or control of any dangerous ordnance, or 18
the materials or parts for making dangerous ordnance, in the 19
absence of circumstances indicating the dangerous ordnance, 20

